title: Selena Gomez releases breakup song 'It Ain't Me' amidst The Weeknd dating rumors
text:
Selena Gomez releases breakup song 'It Ain't Me' amidst The Weeknd dating rumors Erin Jensen, USA TODAY 10:14 a.m. ET Feb. 16, 2017 
Selena Gomez has gifted the world with its latest breakup anthem. Wednesday evening, the singer let her more than 46 million Twitter followers know that her new song, It Ain't Me , is "finally here!" It's finally here! Listen to my new song #ItAintMe with @KygoMusic on @AppleMusic ! https://t.co/jBKYNmM4GY â€” Selena Gomez (@selenagomez) February 16, 2017 
Though the collaboration with Norwegian music producer Kygo deals with a very taxing ex, the song's upbeat rhythm makes it great for dancing away a toxic relationship. 
"Somewhere along the lines/We stopped seeing eye to eye/You were staying out all night/And I had enough," Gomez sings in the lyrics and continues, "No, I don't wanna know where you been or where you're going/But I know I won't be home/And you'll be on your own." 
For Jelena theorists, this might conjure up the image of Gomez's famous ex, Justin Bieber , whom she confirmed she was dating on The Ellen DeGeneres Show in 2011 after the two attended Vanity Fair's Oscar party that same year. 
Young love at the 'Vanity Fair' Oscar Party on Feb. 27, 2011. (Photo: Carlo Allegri, AP) 
The years following have been peppered with rumors of splits, reunions and sightings, as if their Facebook relationship status permanently reads, "It's complicated." In 2015, the Sorry singer told Access Hollywood of his ex, "I'm never going to stop loving her." 
As for Gomez, she's recently been spotted kissing The Weeknd , who has some seemingly pointed lyrics of his own. Featured on a song with Nav titled Some Way, the Starboy sings of taking another's woman. 
"I think your girl, think your girl, fell in love with me," and "I just took that chick, and I know you feelin' some way" are a few of the lyrics he sings. 
Though not confirmed, the words have suspicious timing considering Bieber told TMZ in January that The Weeknd's music is "wack." Read or Share this story: http://usat.ly/2lbBZ9l Most Popular
